1
00:00:37,115 --> 00:00:38,825
EPISODE 10

2
00:00:40,326 --> 00:00:42,412
A Chinese restaurant owner.

3
00:00:43,830 --> 00:00:45,206
Better than I expected.

4
00:00:47,625 --> 00:00:51,211
Hey, what are you doing?
We meet after ten years.

5
00:00:51,212 --> 00:00:54,715
Even if you can't pretend to be happy,
shouldn't you at least offer me some tea?

6
00:00:56,259 --> 00:00:59,636
I don't think we're on terms
to sit and have tea.

7
00:00:59,637 --> 00:01:01,847
Hey, no need to be so guarded.

8
00:01:01,848 --> 00:01:04,599
I just came to see how you were doing.

9
00:01:06,269 --> 00:01:07,979
I was always curious.

10
00:01:08,438 --> 00:01:10,731
The traitor to his country,
Jeong Ho-myeong.

11
00:01:11,065 --> 00:01:14,569
How miserably is he living?

12
00:01:15,611 --> 00:01:18,489
But here you are with a cute son

13
00:01:18,739 --> 00:01:22,452
and doing better than I expected.
Good for you.

14
00:01:22,618 --> 00:01:24,871
Leave my family out of this.

15
00:01:26,747 --> 00:01:28,249
I didn't mean anything by it.

16
00:01:28,666 --> 00:01:32,837
I was just happy to see
that a junior I was fond of is doing well.

17
00:01:33,254 --> 00:01:35,590
Oh, right. Come to think of it

18
00:01:36,132 --> 00:01:38,134
there was another junior I was fond of.

19
00:01:42,180 --> 00:01:44,140
Team Leader Jo Seong-won, I mean.

20
00:01:45,266 --> 00:01:46,476
What a shame.

21
00:01:46,976 --> 00:01:50,438
If it weren't
for that pathetic sense of justice

22
00:01:50,897 --> 00:01:53,858
he'd have a good position
at the NIS by now

23
00:01:54,859 --> 00:01:57,777
and be living comfortably.

24
00:01:57,778 --> 00:02:00,907
Instead, his leg is ruined,
and he's a drifter.

25
00:02:01,407 --> 00:02:05,203
It's a real shame, isn't it?

26
00:02:07,121 --> 00:02:08,538
Ho-myeong.

27
00:02:09,122 --> 00:02:12,335
Ten years ago and even now

28
00:02:13,920 --> 00:02:15,755
you could have just let it go.

29
00:02:16,547 --> 00:02:20,510
Why do you have to make things
so complicated?

30
00:02:22,512 --> 00:02:26,349
This time as well,
do you and everyone around you

31
00:02:27,350 --> 00:02:29,519
have to be destroyed
before you learn your lesson?

32
00:02:39,278 --> 00:02:40,947
This isn't like you.

33
00:02:41,656 --> 00:02:44,533
- What?
- Coming here in person

34
00:02:44,534 --> 00:02:47,912
and making threats
using my family and Jo Seong-won.

35
00:02:48,663 --> 00:02:51,706
The Han Gyeong-wook I knew
at the National Intelligence Service

36
00:02:51,707 --> 00:02:53,416
wasn't the type

37
00:02:53,417 --> 00:02:56,587
to give friendly warnings
when something got in his way.

38
00:02:57,338 --> 00:02:59,382
He would have just wiped it all out.

39
00:03:11,978 --> 00:03:14,355
So why are you acting this way?

40
00:03:16,607 --> 00:03:20,570
It suddenly reminds me
of something you drilled into me.

41
00:03:20,945 --> 00:03:23,238
When infiltrating enemy lines,
maintain total situational awareness.

42
00:03:23,239 --> 00:03:26,409
Especially, pay close attention
to the enemy's armaments.

43
00:03:27,535 --> 00:03:29,620
Whatever the enemy might be holding
in their hands

44
00:03:29,954 --> 00:03:31,664
never take your eyes off them.

45
00:03:34,709 --> 00:03:35,876
You remember, don't you?

46
00:03:36,794 --> 00:03:38,379
Yes.

47
00:03:38,838 --> 00:03:42,717
I'm glad to see my lessons stuck with you.

48
00:03:44,176 --> 00:03:45,386
But, Ho-myeong.

49
00:03:46,387 --> 00:03:47,597
Do I really

50
00:03:48,598 --> 00:03:50,600
need to be on guard around you?

51
00:03:51,058 --> 00:03:54,437
Well, if you have something to hide,
then I suppose you should be.

52
00:03:56,564 --> 00:04:00,943
You've changed a lot.
Making such pathetic threats.

53
00:04:01,068 --> 00:04:04,280
Why don't you find out for yourself
if they're pathetic or not?

54
00:04:09,702 --> 00:04:13,205
You seem to have a big misunderstanding.

55
00:04:14,624 --> 00:04:15,875
I didn't

56
00:04:17,459 --> 00:04:19,670
come here to negotiate with you.

57
00:04:22,715 --> 00:04:24,967
I have no intention of negotiating either.

58
00:04:25,885 --> 00:04:27,720
I'm simply informing you.

59
00:04:28,304 --> 00:04:30,056
Since you seem to be in the dark
about something.

60
00:04:37,855 --> 00:04:38,898
Good grief.

61
00:04:39,899 --> 00:04:42,317
There's no point
in talking about this anymore.

62
00:04:42,318 --> 00:04:45,029
Yes, I agree this conversation
has gone on for too long.

63
00:04:46,364 --> 00:04:47,573
Fine.

64
00:04:48,115 --> 00:04:51,118
If you're so determined
to see this through to the end

65
00:04:51,661 --> 00:04:53,286
I'll give you what you want.

66
00:04:53,287 --> 00:04:54,664
See you around, Ho-myeong.

67
00:04:55,790 --> 00:04:56,916
Oh, right.

68
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:02,004
And give my regards
to Team Leader Jo Seong-won.

69
00:05:21,482 --> 00:05:25,110
Ho-myeong. Hey, that man who just left...

70
00:05:25,111 --> 00:05:26,737
That was Han Gyeong-wook, right?

71
00:05:26,946 --> 00:05:31,075
I heard you were an NIS agent.
Did you know him?

72
00:05:41,043 --> 00:05:42,169
So then

73
00:05:43,754 --> 00:05:47,341
the person who framed the Director
and forced you to resign

74
00:05:47,842 --> 00:05:50,428
was the other candidate, Han Gyeong-wook?

75
00:05:51,303 --> 00:05:52,471
That's right.

76
00:05:53,389 --> 00:05:55,932
Chairman Do of Heaven Capital
and Heaven Casino

77
00:05:55,933 --> 00:05:58,978
and Candidate Han Gyeong-wook
are all in it together.

78
00:06:01,063 --> 00:06:05,067
Those guys are plotting something
on Yeongseon Island.

79
00:06:08,404 --> 00:06:12,198
That day, without any real explanation

80
00:06:12,199 --> 00:06:15,578
I suddenly told you to stop
helping the victims.

81
00:06:16,495 --> 00:06:19,289
- I'm sorry about that.
- Oh, no, Mr. Kim.

82
00:06:19,290 --> 00:06:21,458
You only said that
because you were worried.

83
00:06:21,459 --> 00:06:22,710
Right.

84
00:06:25,671 --> 00:06:27,089
But, O-ran

85
00:06:28,007 --> 00:06:30,633
I'm telling you this
because I'm truly worried.

86
00:06:30,634 --> 00:06:31,761
Any further than this

87
00:06:32,553 --> 00:06:34,305
don't try to do anything.

88
00:06:34,847 --> 00:06:38,434
This isn't just a matter
of helping the victims.

89
00:06:39,477 --> 00:06:41,437
If they find out about this

90
00:06:42,146 --> 00:06:45,149
you and the others
who are interfering with their business

91
00:06:45,691 --> 00:06:47,318
and even the people around you...

92
00:06:49,028 --> 00:06:50,863
They will never leave you alone.

93
00:06:55,618 --> 00:06:59,078
Jeong Ho-myeong came to see me yesterday.

94
00:06:59,079 --> 00:07:01,373
Oh, yes, I heard.

95
00:07:03,709 --> 00:07:07,296
About what happened
to your husband in the past...

96
00:07:08,088 --> 00:07:09,507
He told me all about it.

97
00:07:09,924 --> 00:07:13,052
He said he knows
exactly what kind of people they are.

98
00:07:14,929 --> 00:07:19,183
He said he would
take care of Han Gyeong-wook himself.

99
00:07:22,061 --> 00:07:24,939
For an NIS agent who's now a civilian

100
00:07:25,439 --> 00:07:28,025
to push himself to take on Han Gyeong-wook

101
00:07:29,610 --> 00:07:31,779
there's a sense of duty, of course.

102
00:07:33,155 --> 00:07:35,406
But the desire to protect his family

103
00:07:35,407 --> 00:07:36,951
must be the biggest reason.

104
00:07:38,035 --> 00:07:39,078
Yes.

105
00:08:20,452 --> 00:08:23,372
- It's been a while, Chairman Hwang.
- It's been a while?

106
00:08:23,956 --> 00:08:27,834
A loyal scumbag like you should just
stay by Deputy Director Han's side.

107
00:08:27,835 --> 00:08:32,046
What brings you all the way out here
on this old man's special day?

108
00:08:32,047 --> 00:08:33,881
And you didn't even bring any tofu.

109
00:08:33,883 --> 00:08:35,592
It's not like you plan on
living a clean life

110
00:08:36,217 --> 00:08:37,469
so what's the point in you eating any?

111
00:08:37,803 --> 00:08:40,139
Well, I guess you have a point.

112
00:08:40,264 --> 00:08:44,393
I'll have to get some blood on my hands
to slit Deputy Director Han's throat.

113
00:08:44,727 --> 00:08:45,936
Right?

114
00:08:48,606 --> 00:08:50,232
What's with that look?

115
00:08:50,441 --> 00:08:52,817
You let me rot in prison for ten years

116
00:08:52,818 --> 00:08:54,319
and now you let me out.

117
00:08:54,320 --> 00:08:56,280
So did you expect me
to bow down in gratitude?

118
00:08:58,741 --> 00:09:00,910
Let's stop with the pointless mind games.

119
00:09:01,243 --> 00:09:02,453
Aren't you curious

120
00:09:02,828 --> 00:09:06,165
about why the Deputy Director let you go?

121
00:09:11,003 --> 00:09:12,504
THE HOLY BIBLE

122
00:09:12,713 --> 00:09:14,882
The Lord has spoken.

123
00:09:15,299 --> 00:09:18,135
Proverbs 18:13.

124
00:09:19,511 --> 00:09:22,305
"To answer before listening

125
00:09:22,306 --> 00:09:25,851
that is folly and shame."

126
00:09:26,352 --> 00:09:30,648
Right. Since the Lord has spoken,
I'll at least hear your reason.

127
00:09:32,733 --> 00:09:34,568
So where's Deputy Director Han now?

128
00:09:34,944 --> 00:09:37,278
ORAN CHINESE RESTAURANT

129
00:09:37,279 --> 00:09:38,530
Mr. Kim.

130
00:09:39,531 --> 00:09:42,034
Hey, O-ran.

131
00:09:42,534 --> 00:09:45,787
What are you doing here?
What if those gangsters followed you?

132
00:09:45,788 --> 00:09:47,538
With Dad and you holding out like this

133
00:09:47,539 --> 00:09:50,084
without even closing up,
how could I not come?

134
00:09:52,086 --> 00:09:54,922
Honestly, your father's so stubborn.

135
00:09:56,256 --> 00:09:57,674
Where's Ho-myeong?

136
00:09:57,675 --> 00:09:59,843
He couldn't persuade your dad,
so he slept here.

137
00:10:01,804 --> 00:10:03,638
Hey, about yesterday.

138
00:10:03,639 --> 00:10:05,723
You know Han Gyeong-wook,
the candidate for mayor of Imcheon?

139
00:10:05,724 --> 00:10:07,184
He came here.

140
00:10:07,726 --> 00:10:09,937
- Han Gyeong-wook?
- Yes.

141
00:10:10,270 --> 00:10:13,231
To be honest, I was skeptical
about Ho-myeong being from the NIS.

142
00:10:13,232 --> 00:10:14,608
But I think it's actually true.

143
00:10:14,858 --> 00:10:16,402
It looked like he was here
to see Ho-myeong.

144
00:10:37,214 --> 00:10:39,550
- What are you doing here?
- Gosh, you scared me.

145
00:10:39,883 --> 00:10:41,093
Why are you here?

146
00:10:41,802 --> 00:10:43,470
We need to talk for a minute.

147
00:10:47,725 --> 00:10:51,311
I heard Han Gyeong-wook
was here yesterday.

148
00:10:51,603 --> 00:10:53,938
He's the one, isn't he?
The one who framed you

149
00:10:53,939 --> 00:10:55,733
and got you kicked out in the past.

150
00:10:56,859 --> 00:10:57,860
Yeah.

151
00:10:58,402 --> 00:10:59,820
Mr. Kim told me

152
00:11:00,571 --> 00:11:03,239
that he's an extremely dangerous person.

153
00:11:03,240 --> 00:11:06,035
Are you going to be okay?

154
00:11:06,827 --> 00:11:08,078
I'm fine.

155
00:11:08,829 --> 00:11:11,497
You, your father, and our Ji-woo...

156
00:11:11,498 --> 00:11:14,042
I'll do whatever it takes to make sure
no harm comes to any of you.

157
00:11:14,043 --> 00:11:15,877
No, I'm not worried about us.
I'm talking about you.

158
00:11:15,878 --> 00:11:17,754
I'm asking if you'll be okay.

159
00:11:17,755 --> 00:11:19,840
Is it okay for you to go up
against someone that dangerous?

160
00:11:22,760 --> 00:11:25,679
What's this? Are you worried about me?

161
00:11:28,140 --> 00:11:31,268
You're our Ji-woo's father.
How could I not be worried?

162
00:11:36,190 --> 00:11:37,983
I've been thinking.

163
00:11:38,901 --> 00:11:41,653
Just like you said, what if all of us

164
00:11:42,196 --> 00:11:44,323
get off Yeongseon Island for a while?

165
00:11:44,448 --> 00:11:46,949
I'll do my best to convince my dad.

166
00:11:46,950 --> 00:11:47,993
No.

167
00:11:48,619 --> 00:11:49,870
I can't go.

168
00:11:50,621 --> 00:11:53,498
I have to resolve this myself,
no matter what.

169
00:11:53,499 --> 00:11:56,501
- No, please don't say that.
- As you've probably heard

170
00:11:56,502 --> 00:12:00,379
Han Gyeong-wook
is planning something on Yeongseon Island.

171
00:12:00,380 --> 00:12:02,423
If that jerk actually becomes mayor

172
00:12:02,424 --> 00:12:05,719
there will be far more victims
than we're seeing now.

173
00:12:07,638 --> 00:12:09,640
I couldn't stop him ten years ago

174
00:12:10,599 --> 00:12:12,476
but this time,
I have to stop him no matter what.

175
00:12:22,903 --> 00:12:24,196
You remember, right?

176
00:12:25,531 --> 00:12:28,158
What you said on the day
our Ji-woo was born.

177
00:12:30,452 --> 00:12:34,957
You said you'd never let Ji-woo
grow up lonely like you did.

178
00:12:35,833 --> 00:12:38,835
That no matter what,
you'd always be by his side

179
00:12:38,836 --> 00:12:41,505
until he became an adult. That promise.

180
00:12:43,382 --> 00:12:44,633
Keep your promise.

181
00:12:52,766 --> 00:12:55,269
I'll find a way to convince my dad.

182
00:12:55,811 --> 00:12:59,064
You just go and take care of
that Han Gyeong-wook guy

183
00:12:59,523 --> 00:13:01,232
and come back.

184
00:13:01,233 --> 00:13:02,568
I'll be waiting.

185
00:13:04,236 --> 00:13:05,487
Okay.

186
00:13:37,352 --> 00:13:39,313
- Did she see us?
- I can't look.

187
00:13:40,063 --> 00:13:42,649
- Is she gone?
- Did she catch on?

188
00:13:43,400 --> 00:13:45,277
How diligent.

189
00:13:49,990 --> 00:13:51,241
Yes, go ahead.

190
00:13:53,118 --> 00:13:54,161
What?

191
00:13:56,413 --> 00:13:58,789
You just said that Han Gyeong-wook came
knowing everything.

192
00:13:58,790 --> 00:14:00,833
Then shouldn't you be lying low for now?

193
00:14:00,834 --> 00:14:03,003
I've bought us some time.

194
00:14:03,587 --> 00:14:06,381
But I think we need to make a move
before he catches on.

195
00:14:06,965 --> 00:14:09,425
Among everything you've found out so far

196
00:14:09,426 --> 00:14:12,720
is there anything that could be
an immediate blow to Han Gyeong-wook?

197
00:14:12,721 --> 00:14:15,015
Well, there's nothing decisive

198
00:14:15,432 --> 00:14:16,808
but I'm starting to get the picture

199
00:14:16,934 --> 00:14:19,394
of what Han Gyeong-wook is up to
on Yeongseon Island.

200
00:14:19,937 --> 00:14:21,772
The Yeongseon Island development project.

201
00:14:22,356 --> 00:14:25,399
It's not as simple
as designating Yeongseon Island

202
00:14:25,400 --> 00:14:27,151
a special tourist zone to develop it.

203
00:14:27,152 --> 00:14:29,655
I don't think its intentions
are so transparent.

204
00:14:30,072 --> 00:14:32,782
You know that company,
Yeongseon Future Development

205
00:14:32,783 --> 00:14:33,991
headed by Do Hyeon-tae?

206
00:14:33,992 --> 00:14:35,285
I looked into it.

207
00:14:36,745 --> 00:14:38,746
The investors
are foreign companies with ties

208
00:14:38,747 --> 00:14:40,748
to the People's Republic of China
and Japan.

209
00:14:40,749 --> 00:14:42,083
And every single one of these companies

210
00:14:42,084 --> 00:14:44,628
is suspected of being involved
with the yakuza.

211
00:14:45,212 --> 00:14:46,255
Isn't that strange?

212
00:14:46,380 --> 00:14:49,006
Why would companies
tied to criminal organizations

213
00:14:49,007 --> 00:14:52,094
jump into the Yeongseon Island
special tourist zone development project?

214
00:14:52,928 --> 00:14:54,387
If they're tied to criminal organizations

215
00:14:54,388 --> 00:14:56,556
this is no longer just a simple
development project.

216
00:14:57,015 --> 00:14:59,268
There must be some other motive.

217
00:15:00,477 --> 00:15:04,106
If I piece together everything
I've figured out so far...

218
00:15:06,191 --> 00:15:07,275
Heaven Capital has been using

219
00:15:07,276 --> 00:15:10,820
illegal debt collection tactics
on Yeongseon Island residents

220
00:15:10,821 --> 00:15:12,155
to secure their land

221
00:15:12,531 --> 00:15:15,116
and using the money
laundered through Heaven Casino

222
00:15:15,117 --> 00:15:18,996
they've been steadily moving forward
with the project behind the scenes.

223
00:15:19,621 --> 00:15:22,290
If Han Gyeong-wook gets elected mayor

224
00:15:22,291 --> 00:15:24,250
he'll lift the regulations
on Yeongseon Island

225
00:15:24,251 --> 00:15:27,546
and push this project forward
full-scale all at once.

226
00:15:27,671 --> 00:15:28,880
So...

227
00:15:30,382 --> 00:15:32,926
We need to do something before that

228
00:15:33,510 --> 00:15:35,720
but there are no traces of Han Gyeong-wook

229
00:15:35,721 --> 00:15:37,556
in either Heaven Capital or Heaven Casino.

230
00:15:37,764 --> 00:15:40,349
I mean, if we could at least prove
that the money from both places

231
00:15:40,350 --> 00:15:43,060
went to Han Gyeong-wook,
or find a record of it

232
00:15:43,061 --> 00:15:44,938
we'd have something to prosecute him with.

233
00:15:46,523 --> 00:15:48,024
You know very well

234
00:15:48,025 --> 00:15:50,235
just how meticulous Han Gyeong-wook is.

235
00:15:51,153 --> 00:15:52,486
It looks like

236
00:15:52,487 --> 00:15:55,824
it will take some time
to secure solid evidence.

237
00:15:58,577 --> 00:16:00,453
The election is right around the corner.

238
00:16:00,454 --> 00:16:02,289
There's no more time to waste.

239
00:16:03,206 --> 00:16:04,833
If it's too difficult for you

240
00:16:04,958 --> 00:16:08,712
- I'll find the evidence my own way.
- Your own way?

241
00:16:09,129 --> 00:16:10,964
I'll tell you after I have it.

242
00:16:12,341 --> 00:16:14,759
Prosecutor, please continue
your investigation

243
00:16:14,760 --> 00:16:16,719
of the people around Han Gyeong-wook.

244
00:16:16,720 --> 00:16:19,430
Okay, I'll contact you right away
if I find anything.

245
00:16:19,431 --> 00:16:20,682
Yes, understood.

246
00:16:29,691 --> 00:16:32,319
Hey, Gang Beom-ryong. It's me.

247
00:16:33,320 --> 00:16:35,489
Bring Bulgae and come
to the camper van right now.

248
00:16:38,033 --> 00:16:40,369
- Chief Kim! Perfect timing.
- Yes.

249
00:16:46,208 --> 00:16:49,293
- About what I mentioned before.
- Yes.

250
00:16:49,294 --> 00:16:51,213
I think we need to speed things up.

251
00:16:51,755 --> 00:16:54,173
Let's dig into the people
around Han Gyeong-wook.

252
00:16:54,174 --> 00:16:55,300
Get all the details.

253
00:16:56,510 --> 00:16:58,970
Prosecutor, I don't think I can do it.

254
00:16:59,346 --> 00:17:02,349
- What?
- The Chief Prosecutor

255
00:17:02,641 --> 00:17:06,228
told me to report your every move
to him without you knowing.

256
00:17:06,395 --> 00:17:11,066
If you give me orders like this,
I have no choice but to report it.

257
00:17:15,779 --> 00:17:17,695
But he told you to do it
without my knowledge.

258
00:17:17,696 --> 00:17:19,615
Are you sure
you should be telling me this?

259
00:17:19,616 --> 00:17:23,618
Because I work with you,
not the Chief Prosecutor.

260
00:17:23,619 --> 00:17:27,374
Even if I get in trouble for it,
I thought it was right to tell you.

261
00:17:30,168 --> 00:17:31,669
Then how about this?

262
00:17:31,670 --> 00:17:34,005
Of all the people around Han Gyeong-wook

263
00:17:34,673 --> 00:17:36,340
let's start with our Chief Prosecutor.

264
00:17:36,341 --> 00:17:38,510
- Yes. What?
- Yes.

265
00:17:39,719 --> 00:17:42,472
Our Chief Prosecutor. My goodness.

266
00:17:43,932 --> 00:17:47,144
I was going to let it slide,
but his constant buzzing

267
00:17:47,894 --> 00:17:49,646
is getting on my nerves.

268
00:17:50,397 --> 00:17:51,982
We need to swat this fly.

269
00:17:52,566 --> 00:17:54,191
You've done this before,
so you'll be good at it, right?

270
00:17:54,192 --> 00:17:56,402
No, this is
completely different from that.

271
00:17:56,403 --> 00:17:59,697
Before, I was tailing someone
connected to the case.

272
00:17:59,698 --> 00:18:02,742
But now you're asking me
to tail my own boss.

273
00:18:02,868 --> 00:18:04,160
It's not different at all.

274
00:18:04,161 --> 00:18:07,289
Our Chief Prosecutor
is deeply involved in this case.

275
00:18:07,414 --> 00:18:10,459
He's taking bribes from Han Gyeong-wook.

276
00:18:11,460 --> 00:18:13,837
Why are you telling me a secret like that?

277
00:18:14,421 --> 00:18:17,006
I'm just going to pretend
I didn't hear that.

278
00:18:17,007 --> 00:18:20,885
I just want to keep my head down
and have a long career. You get me?

279
00:18:20,886 --> 00:18:22,846
Chief Kim, wait.

280
00:18:22,971 --> 00:18:27,766
If you want that long career,
you have to cut that rotten lifeline.

281
00:18:27,767 --> 00:18:31,021
And make a new, sturdy,
and safe one for yourself.

282
00:18:31,521 --> 00:18:35,108
Don't you see what's at stake here?

283
00:18:36,526 --> 00:18:38,945
You'll approve my overtime, right?

284
00:18:39,863 --> 00:18:42,449
But what's Mr. Jeong thinking?

285
00:18:43,200 --> 00:18:44,450
He was so suspicious of him

286
00:18:44,451 --> 00:18:46,494
and now he wants us
to bring Bong Je-sun to the camper?

287
00:18:46,495 --> 00:18:48,872
Gosh, how am I supposed to know
what he's thinking?

288
00:18:49,456 --> 00:18:51,957
Oh, right. Was everything okay
on Mi-kyung's end?

289
00:18:51,958 --> 00:18:55,879
What's there to report?
Everything's quiet.

290
00:18:59,841 --> 00:19:01,176
- Hey.
- Hello.

291
00:19:01,301 --> 00:19:02,302
Hello.

292
00:19:06,181 --> 00:19:08,933
- What's that?
- Oh, this?

293
00:19:08,934 --> 00:19:11,393
You're working so hard
to help me get my memory back

294
00:19:11,394 --> 00:19:14,397
so I wanted to help out somehow
and brought a few things.

295
00:19:15,398 --> 00:19:16,566
You really overdo it.

296
00:19:17,275 --> 00:19:18,276
What?

297
00:19:21,738 --> 00:19:24,407
Hey, it's you, isn't it?
From the warehouse.

298
00:19:25,033 --> 00:19:27,494
- The warehouse?
- Yes. Don't you remember?

299
00:19:28,495 --> 00:19:32,164
You know, back when those
Heaven Capital goons dragged us away.

300
00:19:32,165 --> 00:19:34,208
Woof, woof!

301
00:19:34,209 --> 00:19:36,126
- Have you lost your mind?
- Are you trying to pick a fight?

302
00:19:36,127 --> 00:19:37,837
No, I'm not trying to pick a fight.

303
00:19:38,255 --> 00:19:40,422
I'm just glad you're okay.

304
00:19:40,423 --> 00:19:43,969
I was so worried
that you'd gotten seriously hurt.

305
00:19:44,261 --> 00:19:46,095
But you're tough, so you seem to be fine.

306
00:19:46,096 --> 00:19:49,139
Stop talking nonsense
and get in while I'm asking nicely.

307
00:19:49,140 --> 00:19:50,474
- Okay?
- Yes.

308
00:19:50,475 --> 00:19:52,519
Hurry. Let's go.

309
00:20:15,417 --> 00:20:18,502
Well, Chairman Hwang,
it's been a long time.

310
00:20:18,503 --> 00:20:20,547
You look even younger
than the last time I saw you.

311
00:20:21,965 --> 00:20:25,719
Isn't that all thanks to you,
Deputy Director Han?

312
00:20:30,682 --> 00:20:33,226
You'll understand the business
once you see read that.

313
00:20:33,977 --> 00:20:36,938
I'll give you 10% of the profits
and give you my full support

314
00:20:37,355 --> 00:20:39,857
in rebuilding your organization.

315
00:20:39,858 --> 00:20:41,191
What do you say?

316
00:20:41,192 --> 00:20:45,029
I'd say that's
more than enough compensation

317
00:20:45,030 --> 00:20:46,364
for spending ten years in prison.

318
00:20:51,953 --> 00:20:54,997
You're not going to use some rat
like Yoo In-gu again

319
00:20:54,998 --> 00:20:57,959
- to stab me in the back, are you?
- Of course not.

320
00:20:58,960 --> 00:21:00,962
As long as the business goes well

321
00:21:01,254 --> 00:21:03,048
why would I have any reason
to do something like that?

322
00:21:07,218 --> 00:21:08,510
What is it?

323
00:21:08,511 --> 00:21:11,430
The reason you're giving me
such a good offer.

324
00:21:11,431 --> 00:21:13,350
You're as sharp as ever.

325
00:21:14,768 --> 00:21:18,188
There's something
I need you to do for me, Chairman Hwang.

326
00:21:28,865 --> 00:21:30,742
One of your men

327
00:21:30,867 --> 00:21:34,579
is in cahoots with that same
NIS agent from ten years ago.

328
00:21:35,330 --> 00:21:36,831
Did you know that?

329
00:21:37,582 --> 00:21:41,586
Those two have the missing package.

330
00:21:44,381 --> 00:21:47,050
So you're saying I should go to Beom-ryong

331
00:21:47,300 --> 00:21:49,344
get that package

332
00:21:50,011 --> 00:21:51,388
and bring it back?

333
00:21:52,263 --> 00:21:56,684
I know it's not easy to get
a runaway child to come back.

334
00:21:56,685 --> 00:21:58,519
If you can't do it, just say so.

335
00:21:58,520 --> 00:22:00,312
Whether by carrot or by stick

336
00:22:00,313 --> 00:22:03,024
all I have to do is bring him home, right?

337
00:22:04,567 --> 00:22:07,445
And recovering the package
shouldn't be too difficult either.

338
00:22:10,573 --> 00:22:12,450
Gosh, so I'm

339
00:22:12,909 --> 00:22:15,370
going into business
with Deputy Director Han.

340
00:22:24,421 --> 00:22:27,215
In return for this fine coffee,
let me give you a gift.

341
00:22:28,383 --> 00:22:31,260
Prosecutor Gang in this photo here

342
00:22:31,261 --> 00:22:32,971
came to see me a while ago.

343
00:22:33,722 --> 00:22:34,806
You...

344
00:22:35,682 --> 00:22:37,182
met with Prosecutor Gang?

345
00:22:37,183 --> 00:22:40,562
She said she would catch the real killer
in Director Kwon Soon-bok's murder case.

346
00:22:41,604 --> 00:22:43,522
I thought she was some kind of psycho

347
00:22:43,523 --> 00:22:45,524
but given the circumstances at the time

348
00:22:45,525 --> 00:22:48,152
I was desperate,
so I took her up on the offer.

349
00:22:48,153 --> 00:22:52,115
I even told Beom-ryong to meet with her.

350
00:22:52,907 --> 00:22:53,991
And?

351
00:22:53,992 --> 00:22:56,034
He never reported back on what happened

352
00:22:56,035 --> 00:22:58,705
so I just assumed it didn't work out
and gave up on it.

353
00:23:00,081 --> 00:23:02,584
But it looks like
things progressed this way.

354
00:23:02,751 --> 00:23:03,835
Right?

355
00:23:06,004 --> 00:23:07,505
Prosecutor Gang.

356
00:23:08,006 --> 00:23:12,176
She may have found out far more
about your shameful secrets

357
00:23:12,177 --> 00:23:15,054
than you might think.

358
00:23:17,974 --> 00:23:19,309
Joong-gi.

359
00:23:20,018 --> 00:23:23,937
We're not far from the finish line.
You know that, right?

360
00:23:23,938 --> 00:23:26,149
- Yes.
- But...

361
00:23:26,733 --> 00:23:29,319
At a time when we should be
making our final push

362
00:23:29,652 --> 00:23:32,738
why do stumbling blocks
like Jeong Ho-myeong or Prosecutor Gang

363
00:23:32,739 --> 00:23:34,282
keep popping up?

364
00:23:34,783 --> 00:23:36,075
I'm sure

365
00:23:36,451 --> 00:23:39,662
I instructed you to clear the path.

366
00:23:40,455 --> 00:23:41,456
I'm sorry.

367
00:23:49,088 --> 00:23:52,090
Before that woman becomes
an even bigger headache

368
00:23:52,091 --> 00:23:54,219
you take care of it on your end.

369
00:23:55,804 --> 00:23:57,555
I'll take care of it
as quickly as possible.

370
00:24:33,800 --> 00:24:35,092
What is it?

371
00:24:35,093 --> 00:24:37,177
What did you drag us out here
to talk about?

372
00:24:37,178 --> 00:24:39,263
Weren't you just complaining
about how this guy is not to be trusted?

373
00:24:39,264 --> 00:24:41,139
Hey, you go on inside.

374
00:24:41,140 --> 00:24:43,059
- What?
- What?

375
00:24:44,352 --> 00:24:46,813
I said go on ahead.
The three of us need to talk.

376
00:24:46,980 --> 00:24:48,147
Okay.

377
00:24:50,859 --> 00:24:53,402
- Go where--
- Where else? Can't you see the door?

378
00:24:53,403 --> 00:24:54,737
Want to jump in the water instead?

379
00:24:55,738 --> 00:24:57,699
I'll be in there, then.

380
00:24:59,909 --> 00:25:00,994
Man, those must be heavy.

381
00:25:23,099 --> 00:25:24,183
You guys.

382
00:25:24,934 --> 00:25:26,352
Now, don't freak out.

383
00:25:30,106 --> 00:25:31,189
Are you serious?

384
00:25:31,190 --> 00:25:32,983
You're saying Han Gyeong-wook
knew everything?

385
00:25:32,984 --> 00:25:34,110
Yes.

386
00:25:34,903 --> 00:25:36,779
He probably thinks we have the package.

387
00:25:37,196 --> 00:25:39,114
I think he'll be back soon.

388
00:25:39,115 --> 00:25:40,741
Well, then we can just
keep pretending we have it.

389
00:25:40,742 --> 00:25:42,034
That won't last long.

390
00:25:42,035 --> 00:25:44,287
He'll catch on quick.
You know what he's like.

391
00:25:45,121 --> 00:25:46,455
Before that happens

392
00:25:46,456 --> 00:25:49,207
we need to find some kind of evidence
of Han Gyeong-wook's wrongdoings

393
00:25:49,208 --> 00:25:50,292
and strike first.

394
00:25:50,293 --> 00:25:52,461
But we don't have much time.
Is that even possible?

395
00:25:52,462 --> 00:25:54,087
We have to try.

396
00:25:54,088 --> 00:25:55,632
If we want to find out quickly

397
00:25:55,965 --> 00:25:58,635
we'll have to dig
into Heaven Capital or Heaven Casino.

398
00:25:59,093 --> 00:26:03,347
But the casino's system
makes it hard to infiltrate.

399
00:26:03,348 --> 00:26:04,974
However, the Heaven Capital business
seems possible.

400
00:26:05,808 --> 00:26:08,769
After Yoo In-gu stepped down

401
00:26:08,770 --> 00:26:11,064
Chairman Do
and that guy, Geum Kang-sik, took over.

402
00:26:14,150 --> 00:26:16,569
- Kang-sik is in charge?
- You know him?

403
00:26:18,655 --> 00:26:19,864
We know him, but...

404
00:26:20,823 --> 00:26:23,076
We're too embarrassed to even admit we do.

405
00:26:25,036 --> 00:26:26,037
Yes, sir.

406
00:26:26,955 --> 00:26:28,539
Kang-sik, the shoes.

407
00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:32,043
Yes, sir.

408
00:26:33,461 --> 00:26:34,462
Here, sir.

409
00:26:44,973 --> 00:26:47,391
- Thank you.
- When we were in the Hwasan Sect

410
00:26:47,392 --> 00:26:49,018
he just shined my shoes.

411
00:26:49,352 --> 00:26:51,312
He was really good
at shining shoes, though.

412
00:26:51,604 --> 00:26:54,356
But he couldn't even manage
a single food stall properly

413
00:26:54,357 --> 00:26:56,025
so he was the epitome of incompetence.

414
00:26:56,901 --> 00:26:58,193
Perfect.

415
00:26:58,194 --> 00:27:01,698
When an incompetent guy takes charge,
things are bound to fall apart.

416
00:27:02,615 --> 00:27:04,783
If we can just squeeze Geum Kang-sik

417
00:27:04,784 --> 00:27:07,494
we can find evidence
that Han ordered the money collection

418
00:27:07,495 --> 00:27:10,123
or find a trail
of where the illegal funds went.

419
00:27:11,040 --> 00:27:13,251
What's so hard about
shaking down Kang-sik?

420
00:27:13,793 --> 00:27:16,963
- Let's do it now.
- You can dismiss Geum Kang-sik

421
00:27:17,130 --> 00:27:18,547
but he's got the other boys.

422
00:27:18,548 --> 00:27:21,884
And he saw what happened to Yoo In-gu,
so he's probably being extremely cautious.

423
00:27:23,302 --> 00:27:27,390
I'm sure he is.
That's why that will be our Plan B.

424
00:27:27,807 --> 00:27:31,727
We have a much more certain way
to take down Han Gyeong-wook.

425
00:27:31,728 --> 00:27:33,813
A more certain way? What is it?

426
00:27:37,650 --> 00:27:40,694
We just have to make Bulgae talk
and get the package.

427
00:27:40,695 --> 00:27:42,446
Are you kidding me?

428
00:27:42,447 --> 00:27:44,698
He says he can't remember anything.
How are you supposed to make him talk?

429
00:27:44,699 --> 00:27:47,160
How many times do I have to tell you?
It's all an act.

430
00:27:49,162 --> 00:27:50,830
Hey, look at him.

431
00:27:51,539 --> 00:27:53,832
Does he really look like Bulgae to you?

432
00:27:53,833 --> 00:27:59,296
Hey, at that K-pop dance place yesterday,
he was living like a total slave.

433
00:27:59,297 --> 00:28:01,466
If he were Bulgae,
why would he live like that?

434
00:28:01,674 --> 00:28:03,968
I also think you've got it wrong.

435
00:28:05,219 --> 00:28:08,306
Do you have any idea how many spies
I dealt with at the NIS?

436
00:28:08,765 --> 00:28:10,224
An act like that...

437
00:28:11,267 --> 00:28:13,686
I just know it when I see it.

438
00:28:15,188 --> 00:28:17,481
You're telling me that
dopey look on his face is all an act?

439
00:28:17,482 --> 00:28:18,774
Just you watch.

440
00:28:18,775 --> 00:28:22,612
I'm going to rip that
detestable Bong Je-sun mask right off him.

441
00:28:27,200 --> 00:28:29,201
He keeps staring over here.

442
00:28:29,202 --> 00:28:30,328
So they think this is funny?

443
00:28:31,329 --> 00:28:32,830
Look at them, having a blast.

444
00:29:14,997 --> 00:29:16,374
Oh, my stomach.

445
00:29:17,333 --> 00:29:18,583
Are you all done talking?

446
00:29:18,584 --> 00:29:20,128
Of course. Why else would we come in?

447
00:29:20,628 --> 00:29:23,214
- Have you made your decision?
- What decision?

448
00:29:24,298 --> 00:29:26,591
Whether you're going to tell the truth now

449
00:29:26,592 --> 00:29:29,219
or keep pretending to be Bong Je-sun.

450
00:29:29,220 --> 00:29:30,388
It's time to decide.

451
00:29:31,347 --> 00:29:34,933
Mr Jeong, just as you're saying

452
00:29:34,934 --> 00:29:38,186
I wish this amnesia were just an act.
I really do.

453
00:29:38,187 --> 00:29:40,523
But I'm telling you,
I really don't remember a thing.

454
00:29:41,858 --> 00:29:42,900
Is that so?

455
00:29:43,860 --> 00:29:45,402
Then let me explain it to you.

456
00:29:45,403 --> 00:29:46,696
What?

457
00:29:47,113 --> 00:29:50,283
Agent Bulgae of the Ministry
of People's Armed Forces.

458
00:29:51,033 --> 00:29:53,451
Dispatched to the South and overseas
for secret operations.

459
00:29:53,452 --> 00:29:57,165
A human weapon trained in North Korea
for various special missions.

460
00:29:57,623 --> 00:30:01,668
Rumored to be a master of disguise
and a Taekkyeon expert.

461
00:30:01,669 --> 00:30:05,381
A legendary spy whose identity
has never been compromised.

462
00:30:06,090 --> 00:30:09,467
A guy like that gets amnesia

463
00:30:09,468 --> 00:30:11,888
and holes up in South Korea for ten years?

464
00:30:13,347 --> 00:30:15,224
Does that make any sense to you?

465
00:30:20,021 --> 00:30:23,900
Believe it or not, it's the truth.

466
00:30:26,652 --> 00:30:28,696
So you're going to stick to that story?

467
00:30:30,781 --> 00:30:32,366
Then I have no choice.

468
00:30:33,784 --> 00:30:37,455
I'll just have to make sure.

469
00:30:38,164 --> 00:30:40,541
Hey, what are you going to do
to make sure?

470
00:30:41,542 --> 00:30:42,793
Watch out!

471
00:31:04,106 --> 00:31:05,691
- Darn.
- Darn it.

472
00:31:07,360 --> 00:31:08,444
What was that?

473
00:31:09,987 --> 00:31:11,988
- What?
- Did you all see that?

474
00:31:11,989 --> 00:31:13,365
You think Bong Je-sun
could have dodged that?

475
00:31:13,366 --> 00:31:15,659
Are you crazy? What if you'd hit him?

476
00:31:15,660 --> 00:31:17,994
Hey, is he a target?
Why do you keep throwing things?

477
00:31:17,995 --> 00:31:19,079
You almost killed him!

478
00:31:19,080 --> 00:31:21,248
I knew he'd dodge it. Because he's Bulgae.

479
00:31:21,249 --> 00:31:22,541
Are you okay?

480
00:31:23,834 --> 00:31:26,211
I don't even know how I dodged that.
I was so shocked.

481
00:31:26,212 --> 00:31:27,837
I barely ducked
my head like this, but right here...

482
00:31:27,838 --> 00:31:29,172
Gosh, it stings.

483
00:31:29,173 --> 00:31:31,217
It's bleeding. I'm bleeding.

484
00:31:31,717 --> 00:31:34,387
- I'm bleeding. Blood!
- What? You punk...

485
00:31:34,512 --> 00:31:36,096
Hey! If you don't want a hole in your head

486
00:31:36,097 --> 00:31:38,723
reveal your identity
and tell me where the package is!

487
00:31:38,724 --> 00:31:41,394
- Mr. Jeong, please stop.
- Yes, you're way too worked up.

488
00:31:41,519 --> 00:31:44,813
So, just because I dodged that,
I'm Bulgae?

489
00:31:44,814 --> 00:31:47,232
Hey, look. You dodged it. See?

490
00:31:47,233 --> 00:31:49,527
He dodged it. He must be Bulgae, right?

491
00:31:50,236 --> 00:31:52,738
Why didn't you dodge this? Why not?

492
00:31:53,155 --> 00:31:54,572
You're calling me Bulgae

493
00:31:54,573 --> 00:31:56,075
for dodging something
most people would dodge?

494
00:31:56,325 --> 00:31:57,994
You've really gone too far. Darn it.

495
00:31:58,244 --> 00:32:01,080
I put up with the soda can. But...

496
00:32:01,497 --> 00:32:03,165
But you throw a knife at a person?

497
00:32:03,332 --> 00:32:06,043
What if I hadn't dodged it?
It came right at me.

498
00:32:06,794 --> 00:32:08,295
Bulgae, my foot.

499
00:32:08,296 --> 00:32:10,714
You can say it a hundred times,
but I still don't remember a thing.

500
00:32:10,715 --> 00:32:14,593
What makes you think I'm acting?
You keep spouting nonsense.

501
00:32:14,927 --> 00:32:17,095
Because none of it makes sense!

502
00:32:17,096 --> 00:32:19,180
For ten years,
with no friends and no girlfriend

503
00:32:19,181 --> 00:32:21,558
you put up with all the crap
at that small company

504
00:32:21,559 --> 00:32:22,767
and spent all your time

505
00:32:22,768 --> 00:32:25,229
looking after
that troublemaker nephew? Why?

506
00:32:25,563 --> 00:32:29,274
If it wasn't an act you'd have
no reason to live like that. Right?

507
00:32:29,275 --> 00:32:32,695
An act? You call this an act?
You think I enjoy living like this?

508
00:32:35,906 --> 00:32:37,825
You think I enjoy any of this?

509
00:32:45,124 --> 00:32:47,168
Nam-il is the only family I have

510
00:32:48,044 --> 00:32:50,503
and I don't even remember
who I used to be.

511
00:32:50,504 --> 00:32:52,506
Do you think it's easy
to get close to people?

512
00:32:52,923 --> 00:32:55,760
The second someone asks
where I'm from, I'm speechless.

513
00:32:56,469 --> 00:32:58,387
The small company? The power trips?

514
00:32:59,347 --> 00:33:01,140
You think anyone enjoys
putting up with that?

515
00:33:02,433 --> 00:33:04,435
At my age, I have no skills
and nowhere else to go.

516
00:33:05,311 --> 00:33:06,937
I'm telling you,
I have nowhere else to go.

517
00:33:11,233 --> 00:33:13,401
Honestly, doesn't he have a point?

518
00:33:13,402 --> 00:33:16,697
What makes you think
Bong Je-sun can just get another job?

519
00:33:17,239 --> 00:33:18,824
I feel the same way.

520
00:33:21,202 --> 00:33:23,954
He said he hasn't dated once
in ten years. How pathetic.

521
00:33:24,288 --> 00:33:26,582
And just look at him.
Who would ever like that face?

522
00:33:27,875 --> 00:33:30,794
And accusing him of being a spy
just because he's unpopular

523
00:33:30,795 --> 00:33:33,798
that just makes us as pathetic as him.

524
00:33:40,304 --> 00:33:41,305
You.

525
00:33:43,516 --> 00:33:44,850
You really...

526
00:33:46,894 --> 00:33:48,145
I've had enough.

527
00:33:49,188 --> 00:33:50,815
- Tie him up.
- What?

528
00:33:51,524 --> 00:33:52,607
Who's he talking about?

529
00:33:52,608 --> 00:33:54,359
Let's just talk this out.

530
00:33:54,360 --> 00:33:55,361
Talk?

531
00:33:55,986 --> 00:33:58,030
Don't you realize what it means
that Han Gyeong-wook came to see me?

532
00:33:58,322 --> 00:33:59,490
You guys...

533
00:33:59,615 --> 00:34:01,700
You saw the Hwasan Sect
get destroyed firsthand.

534
00:34:02,868 --> 00:34:04,703
You want to be careless
and go through the same thing again?

535
00:34:12,628 --> 00:34:14,129
- Are you okay?
- Yes. Gosh!

536
00:34:14,130 --> 00:34:15,380
Does it hurt a lot?

537
00:34:18,426 --> 00:34:19,592
So, what are you going to do?

538
00:34:20,052 --> 00:34:21,137
You're not going to do
anything crazy, are you?

539
00:34:21,887 --> 00:34:24,348
Oh no. That's... that's the truth serum.

540
00:34:24,974 --> 00:34:26,141
Truth serum?

541
00:34:26,891 --> 00:34:28,851
It's a drug used by the CIA.

542
00:34:28,853 --> 00:34:31,813
Once you're injected,
you'll tell the truth within ten minutes

543
00:34:31,813 --> 00:34:34,732
but there's a 50% chance
you'll spend your life drooling.

544
00:34:34,733 --> 00:34:36,025
It's a deadly poison.

545
00:34:36,152 --> 00:34:38,237
I didn't want to resort to this

546
00:34:38,737 --> 00:34:41,114
but if you're going to keep this up,
I have no choice.

547
00:34:42,116 --> 00:34:44,199
- You're kidding, right?
- I'm serious.

548
00:34:44,201 --> 00:34:46,786
- Darn it.
- Hey, Jeong Ho-myeong.

549
00:34:46,786 --> 00:34:48,580
Now you're resorting to drugs?

550
00:34:48,581 --> 00:34:50,498
Are you human? Are you serious?

551
00:34:50,498 --> 00:34:52,126
Shut it, you thug.

552
00:34:59,133 --> 00:35:00,259
Bulgae.

553
00:35:00,885 --> 00:35:02,886
This is your last chance. Think carefully.

554
00:35:02,887 --> 00:35:04,721
I'm not doing this
because of a personal grudge.

555
00:35:04,722 --> 00:35:06,556
If you keep lying,
the people of Yeongseon Island

556
00:35:06,557 --> 00:35:08,225
the dance club members,
your nephew Heo Nam-il

557
00:35:08,350 --> 00:35:09,810
and Prosecutor Gang will all be in danger.

558
00:35:10,603 --> 00:35:13,689
So just tell me now. It's not too late.

559
00:35:22,198 --> 00:35:24,658
You seriously think
that'll bring back my memories?

560
00:35:25,242 --> 00:35:27,328
What are you all doing?
Have you all gone insane?

561
00:35:27,620 --> 00:35:29,455
Are you just going to
stand there and watch?

562
00:35:29,997 --> 00:35:33,000
That was your last chance. So be it.

563
00:35:33,667 --> 00:35:36,962
Take one more step
and this thug will beat you up.

564
00:35:37,087 --> 00:35:40,089
- Two steps, three steps, four steps.
- No!

565
00:35:40,090 --> 00:35:41,759
Let go of me!

566
00:35:44,178 --> 00:35:45,888
Wait!

567
00:35:49,975 --> 00:35:51,059
Let go of me.

568
00:35:51,060 --> 00:35:53,937
You're out of your mind. Stop!

569
00:35:53,938 --> 00:35:56,648
I said let go!
You know I hate being touched, right?

570
00:35:56,649 --> 00:35:59,567
- Are you with the NIS or the CIA?
- Do you even know what CIA is?

571
00:35:59,568 --> 00:36:01,486
- This is dangerous!
- Do you know the CIA, you punk?

572
00:36:01,487 --> 00:36:03,071
- Stop it!
- You lunatic!

573
00:36:03,072 --> 00:36:05,532
- Let go of me, you punk!
- It's too dangerous!

574
00:36:05,533 --> 00:36:07,117
Stop!

575
00:36:12,248 --> 00:36:13,332
Do it.

576
00:36:14,625 --> 00:36:15,917
What?

577
00:36:15,918 --> 00:36:18,087
Just inject me with that syringe.

578
00:36:19,463 --> 00:36:21,423
No matter how many times I tell you
I've lost my memory

579
00:36:21,840 --> 00:36:23,925
you have no intention of listening.

580
00:36:23,926 --> 00:36:25,760
Throwing knives at people

581
00:36:25,761 --> 00:36:27,679
and threatening them with your crude talk.

582
00:36:27,680 --> 00:36:29,055
What you guys are doing right now...

583
00:36:29,056 --> 00:36:32,309
How is this any different
from what that Han Gyeong-wook guy does?

584
00:36:33,435 --> 00:36:35,896
You might as well just inject me.

585
00:36:37,606 --> 00:36:38,857
Inject me and...

586
00:36:40,234 --> 00:36:43,362
Yes, go on and hear
what this so-called truth is.

587
00:36:44,989 --> 00:36:46,824
Just do it. Inject me.

588
00:36:54,873 --> 00:36:58,627
- Mr. Jeong!
- Do you still want to go through with it?

589
00:37:06,302 --> 00:37:08,637
Look me straight in the eye.

590
00:37:14,393 --> 00:37:15,644
You really...

591
00:37:16,312 --> 00:37:18,230
don't have a single memory as Bulgae?

592
00:37:20,232 --> 00:37:23,152
I told you.
How many times do I have to say it?

593
00:37:23,569 --> 00:37:26,404
How many darn times do I have to tell you?

594
00:37:26,405 --> 00:37:28,531
I don't remember.

595
00:37:28,532 --> 00:37:30,409
So why are you calling me a liar?

596
00:37:31,660 --> 00:37:33,329
- Hey, Gong-bok. Here.
- Okay.

597
00:37:33,495 --> 00:37:34,663
That's enough.

598
00:37:36,373 --> 00:37:38,082
Keep it up. You're doing great.

599
00:37:38,083 --> 00:37:41,253
- You idiot.
- Just stop it already.

600
00:37:48,886 --> 00:37:49,970
Fine.

601
00:37:50,638 --> 00:37:52,348
Well, if he still denies it after all this

602
00:37:53,807 --> 00:37:57,144
- I guess that's true.
- Yes. Mr. Jeong Ho-myeong.

603
00:37:58,729 --> 00:38:00,104
- Are you okay?
- Yes, I'm fine.

604
00:38:00,105 --> 00:38:01,565
- Does it hurt a lot?
- Yes.

605
00:38:04,985 --> 00:38:08,113
Oh, and that shot from before?
It was this.

606
00:38:09,114 --> 00:38:11,033
- What?
- What did you say, you fool?

607
00:38:12,201 --> 00:38:14,410
Hey, Bulgae. No, Bong Je-sun.

608
00:38:14,411 --> 00:38:15,412
My bad.

609
00:38:16,080 --> 00:38:18,374
You're a good guy, so you'll understand.

610
00:38:22,002 --> 00:38:23,253
Darn it, seriously.

611
00:38:25,214 --> 00:38:27,090
- Are you okay?
- Thanks for saving me.

612
00:38:27,091 --> 00:38:28,716
- Untie him, quick.
- Oh, yes.

613
00:38:28,717 --> 00:38:30,594
That darn devil, Jeong Ho-myeong.

614
00:38:35,474 --> 00:38:37,059
He tied this really tight.

615
00:38:37,976 --> 00:38:40,312
A master of disguise
and a Taekkyeon expert...

616
00:38:42,690 --> 00:38:44,858
Okay, let's think about this.

617
00:38:45,567 --> 00:38:49,113
This guy who's some kind of
martial arts master or whatever

618
00:38:49,488 --> 00:38:52,115
seems to be a trained North Korean spy.

619
00:38:52,116 --> 00:38:55,743
The other is Gang Beom-ryong,
the former number two of the Hwasan Sect.

620
00:38:55,744 --> 00:38:57,078
And the last one

621
00:38:57,079 --> 00:39:00,916
is some agent from the NIS
who knows Han Gyeong-wook well.

622
00:39:02,751 --> 00:39:04,836
What kind of combination is this?

623
00:39:04,837 --> 00:39:07,046
What kind of scheme are they plotting

624
00:39:07,047 --> 00:39:08,590
that brought these three together?

625
00:39:10,050 --> 00:39:11,635
A North Korean spy

626
00:39:12,720 --> 00:39:16,181
the National Intelligence Service,
and Gang Beom-ryong.

627
00:39:18,684 --> 00:39:21,770
Oh, now that you mention it, ten years ago

628
00:39:22,062 --> 00:39:25,231
Deputy Director Han
came to see Chairman Hwang.

629
00:39:25,232 --> 00:39:27,066
He wanted to work together on a job.

630
00:39:27,067 --> 00:39:28,317
A job?

631
00:39:28,318 --> 00:39:31,238
He asked us to find him
a solid guy back then.

632
00:39:31,697 --> 00:39:34,825
I remember Gang Beom-ryong
and Ma Gong-bok were assigned to it.

633
00:39:36,493 --> 00:39:37,536
So...

634
00:39:38,412 --> 00:39:40,789
- they acted on an order?
- Yes.

635
00:39:41,290 --> 00:39:44,251
- So, what happened with that job?
- Well...

636
00:39:44,835 --> 00:39:47,671
Right after that job, Deputy Director Han

637
00:39:48,255 --> 00:39:50,965
and Yoo In-gu teamed up
and backstabbed the chairman.

638
00:39:50,966 --> 00:39:53,259
So whether they succeeded or what...

639
00:39:53,260 --> 00:39:55,094
I don't really know that part.

640
00:39:55,095 --> 00:39:59,056
I bet that order was the ferry case.

641
00:39:59,057 --> 00:40:01,142
And that must be when those three

642
00:40:01,143 --> 00:40:03,061
and Deputy Director Han
got involved with each other.

643
00:40:03,479 --> 00:40:07,482
Considering how Han Gyeong-wook
is still paying special attention to this

644
00:40:07,483 --> 00:40:09,567
it seems like something major

645
00:40:09,568 --> 00:40:12,070
must have happened on that ferry.

646
00:40:13,322 --> 00:40:16,074
Darn, what could it be?

647
00:40:17,868 --> 00:40:20,787
Mr. Nam, you said you had
a contact at the NIS, right?

648
00:40:20,788 --> 00:40:21,996
- Yes.
- Okay.

649
00:40:21,997 --> 00:40:23,790
Then can you find out

650
00:40:23,791 --> 00:40:25,416
what happened ten years ago

651
00:40:25,417 --> 00:40:27,377
- about this ferry case?
- Yes.

652
00:40:30,214 --> 00:40:31,256
What?

653
00:40:32,216 --> 00:40:33,258
It's Secretary Baek.

654
00:40:36,637 --> 00:40:38,554
- Yes?
- Chairman Do.

655
00:40:38,555 --> 00:40:40,348
You haven't forgotten
tomorrow's delivery, have you?

656
00:40:40,349 --> 00:40:41,517
Of course not.

657
00:40:42,226 --> 00:40:43,392
But what about it?

658
00:40:43,393 --> 00:40:45,229
The Deputy Director says
he has something to tell you

659
00:40:45,479 --> 00:40:46,729
and asks you to come in today.

660
00:40:46,730 --> 00:40:50,067
Today? Yes, understood.

661
00:40:52,361 --> 00:40:53,946
Something to tell me?

662
00:40:55,113 --> 00:40:57,658
What a roundabout way
of telling me to hurry up with the money.

663
00:40:58,075 --> 00:41:01,119
Mr. Nam, go to Mr. Geum's Capital
and get the bag.

664
00:41:01,495 --> 00:41:03,455
What? The bag?

665
00:41:29,606 --> 00:41:30,899
It's a green juice.

666
00:41:31,358 --> 00:41:34,235
It's said to help with fatigue
and clear your head.

667
00:41:34,236 --> 00:41:35,654
Here, drink this.

668
00:41:41,034 --> 00:41:42,410
Fine, don't drink it.

669
00:41:42,411 --> 00:41:44,204
It's not like I'm giving it to you
because I like you.

670
00:41:58,343 --> 00:42:00,095
I'm sorry.

671
00:42:01,179 --> 00:42:04,850
For being just Bong Je-sun
and not the human weapon, Bulgae.

672
00:42:06,393 --> 00:42:07,895
You know

673
00:42:08,020 --> 00:42:10,105
I don't think I've ever felt

674
00:42:11,023 --> 00:42:14,067
as frustrated about my amnesia
as I do today.

675
00:42:15,444 --> 00:42:19,239
The people on Yeongseon Island
and Nam-il could all be in danger.

676
00:42:20,699 --> 00:42:23,994
I'm sure there's a clue
in my memories that could save them

677
00:42:24,620 --> 00:42:26,496
so why did I forget everything?

678
00:42:27,331 --> 00:42:29,416
I can't even remember the faintest detail.

679
00:42:35,380 --> 00:42:38,425
It's not that
I don't understand you, Mr. Jeong.

680
00:42:39,009 --> 00:42:42,429
If there's any other way I can help,
please tell me.

681
00:42:42,596 --> 00:42:45,599
Then I'll do anything. Anything.

682
00:42:50,938 --> 00:42:52,356
Well, isn't this lovely?

683
00:42:54,191 --> 00:42:55,734
Hey, you guys stay here.

684
00:42:56,568 --> 00:42:59,571
- Why? Are you going somewhere?
- Finding the package is a lost cause.

685
00:42:59,738 --> 00:43:02,616
I have to go with Plan B
I mentioned earlier.

686
00:43:03,241 --> 00:43:05,159
I'll head over to Heaven Capital

687
00:43:05,160 --> 00:43:07,287
so you guys stay here
and work with Bulgae...

688
00:43:10,165 --> 00:43:11,248
I mean work with Bong Je-sun

689
00:43:11,249 --> 00:43:13,794
and make a list of places
where the package could be.

690
00:43:13,919 --> 00:43:15,294
Places where the package could be?

691
00:43:15,295 --> 00:43:19,341
Every single place Bong Je-sun went to
while he lived on Yeongseon Island.

692
00:43:20,759 --> 00:43:22,385
Starting tomorrow,
we'll split into two teams.

693
00:43:22,386 --> 00:43:24,011
One team will take Heaven Capital

694
00:43:24,012 --> 00:43:26,180
and the other team will take the receiver

695
00:43:26,181 --> 00:43:27,807
and comb through Yeongseon Island.

696
00:43:27,808 --> 00:43:28,975
You never know.

697
00:43:28,976 --> 00:43:30,310
We might find something.

698
00:43:31,937 --> 00:43:34,355
- Okay.
- You can help with that, right?

699
00:43:34,356 --> 00:43:36,233
Yes, I'll do it.

700
00:43:38,402 --> 00:43:41,113
Open the cabinet next to the bed.
The receiver should be in there.

701
00:44:10,392 --> 00:44:12,685
Things are a little tight this month.

702
00:44:12,686 --> 00:44:15,564
I have to pay my guys too.
Just one more month.

703
00:44:16,481 --> 00:44:17,606
Give me an extension.

704
00:44:17,607 --> 00:44:19,775
You know perfectly well
that laundry payments

705
00:44:19,776 --> 00:44:21,111
have to be delivered on time.

706
00:44:21,820 --> 00:44:25,156
- You didn't know?
- I know. But...

707
00:44:25,157 --> 00:44:27,158
Come on, just help me out this once.

708
00:44:27,159 --> 00:44:29,369
These are Deputy Director Han's orders.

709
00:44:29,870 --> 00:44:32,247
Our hands are tied, you get me?

710
00:44:32,789 --> 00:44:35,000
See you around, President Geum.

711
00:44:47,804 --> 00:44:48,889
Boss.

712
00:44:50,057 --> 00:44:53,643
Did they really take everything?
The guys are really unhappy.

713
00:44:53,894 --> 00:44:56,021
At least when Yoo In-gu was around,
our paychecks were never late.

714
00:44:56,188 --> 00:44:57,314
Everyone's saying
the old days were better.

715
00:45:01,234 --> 00:45:03,403
What are you looking at, you punks?
Get to work!

716
00:45:04,529 --> 00:45:06,823
What? Yoo In-gu?

717
00:45:08,492 --> 00:45:10,619
Which one of you bastards
said that crap? Damn it.

718
00:45:12,037 --> 00:45:13,205
Hey.

719
00:45:13,663 --> 00:45:16,791
Who do you think saved this organization
after Yoo In-gu nearly destroyed it?

720
00:45:16,792 --> 00:45:18,292
The organization is struggling

721
00:45:18,293 --> 00:45:20,796
and you're driving around
in a nice car by yourself.

722
00:45:20,921 --> 00:45:23,256
The guys only say that
because it's what they see.

723
00:45:25,884 --> 00:45:28,762
Hey, I take the bus
just to save money on gas.

724
00:45:29,346 --> 00:45:32,306
Not me. It was the other guys.

725
00:45:32,307 --> 00:45:33,308
Whatever. Forget it.

726
00:45:35,685 --> 00:45:38,188
Hey, just keep the guys in line.

727
00:45:38,396 --> 00:45:40,564
I'll figure out a way
to get them paid. Got it?

728
00:45:40,565 --> 00:45:43,360
- Yes, Boss.
- Get out of here. Go away.

729
00:45:54,454 --> 00:45:55,789
You're right on time.

730
00:45:56,790 --> 00:45:59,626
Chairman Hwang,
this is Chairman Do Hyeon-tae.

731
00:45:59,835 --> 00:46:02,838
Chairman Do,
this is Chairman Hwang Hwa-san.

732
00:46:04,005 --> 00:46:06,090
I'm Hwang Hwa-san, Chairman Do.

733
00:46:06,091 --> 00:46:07,092
I'm Do Hyeon-tae.

734
00:46:07,509 --> 00:46:11,178
Could you be from the Hwasan Sect?

735
00:46:11,179 --> 00:46:12,347
Oh, my.

736
00:46:12,681 --> 00:46:15,976
For someone like you
to recognize an old man like me.

737
00:46:16,393 --> 00:46:17,561
I'm honored.

738
00:46:18,770 --> 00:46:20,021
Not at all.

739
00:46:20,355 --> 00:46:21,982
- Please, have a seat.
- Yes.

740
00:46:29,156 --> 00:46:30,281
We'll register Chairman Hwang

741
00:46:30,282 --> 00:46:32,741
as a director
of Yeongseon Future Development

742
00:46:32,742 --> 00:46:35,287
and he'll be in charge of
the Heaven Capital business from now on.

743
00:46:36,872 --> 00:46:39,499
But we've been handling that
just fine on our end.

744
00:46:40,041 --> 00:46:42,459
Why go through all the trouble?
We could just...

745
00:46:42,460 --> 00:46:44,670
Chairman Do,
you have way too much on your plate

746
00:46:44,671 --> 00:46:47,590
with the hotel, casino,
and the Yeongseon Island project.

747
00:46:47,591 --> 00:46:49,258
We need to be efficient.

748
00:46:49,259 --> 00:46:51,511
Think of it as going back
to how things were under Yoo In-gu.

749
00:46:54,431 --> 00:46:56,141
How things were under Yoo In-gu?

750
00:46:56,641 --> 00:46:57,684
Oh, and...

751
00:46:58,393 --> 00:47:02,981
Let's wrap up the case
you were following as well.

752
00:47:03,732 --> 00:47:06,276
That kind of work
is Chairman Hwang's specialty, after all.

753
00:47:12,324 --> 00:47:13,366
Understood.

754
00:47:14,367 --> 00:47:16,786
Having you here, Chairman,
takes a huge weight off my shoulders.

755
00:47:16,912 --> 00:47:21,124
From now on, if you run into any trouble,
just say the word.

756
00:47:21,791 --> 00:47:23,792
We're on the same team now, after all.

757
00:47:23,793 --> 00:47:27,546
I'll give it my all. I'm here to help.

758
00:47:27,547 --> 00:47:29,715
Thank you.
I look forward to learning from you.

759
00:47:29,716 --> 00:47:31,009
Of course.

760
00:47:42,604 --> 00:47:44,855
He thinks he can sideline me

761
00:47:44,856 --> 00:47:46,650
by putting some washed-up
old geezer in charge?

762
00:47:47,067 --> 00:47:50,070
I do all the hard work,
and that guy reaps the benefits.

763
00:47:52,322 --> 00:47:54,406
What do you think, Mr. Nam?

764
00:47:54,407 --> 00:47:56,159
I believe we need to take action.

765
00:47:56,910 --> 00:47:59,996
If profits from Heaven Capital
start dropping tomorrow

766
00:48:00,580 --> 00:48:02,122
it'll disrupt our cash flow.

767
00:48:02,123 --> 00:48:05,209
It's not just about the money.

768
00:48:05,210 --> 00:48:07,127
I have a really bad feeling about this.

769
00:48:07,128 --> 00:48:09,213
No matter how I look at it,
this is a signal from Deputy Director Han

770
00:48:09,214 --> 00:48:10,423
that he doesn't trust me.

771
00:48:10,757 --> 00:48:13,634
If I just sit back,
I'll end up just like Yoo In-gu.

772
00:48:13,635 --> 00:48:15,844
Surely Deputy Director Han
wouldn't do that, would he?

773
00:48:15,845 --> 00:48:17,639
I know Han Gyeong-wook very well.

774
00:48:19,432 --> 00:48:21,518
Keep the hitmen on standby.

775
00:48:23,186 --> 00:48:26,564
And if you find even the smallest lead
on Deputy Director Han

776
00:48:26,856 --> 00:48:29,191
tell them to contact me right away.

777
00:48:29,192 --> 00:48:30,193
Yes, sir.

778
00:48:35,532 --> 00:48:37,408
Hey, it's an emergency.

779
00:48:37,409 --> 00:48:39,286
I said I'd pay you back right away!

780
00:48:39,786 --> 00:48:40,829
Hey, hold on.

781
00:48:43,498 --> 00:48:45,083
What's going on?

782
00:48:59,347 --> 00:49:01,599
Long time no see, kid.

783
00:49:02,851 --> 00:49:04,185
Boss!

784
00:49:11,985 --> 00:49:13,695
President Geum Kang-sik.

785
00:49:14,279 --> 00:49:16,613
Live long enough and you see everything.

786
00:49:16,614 --> 00:49:18,073
Both you and Yoo In-gu...

787
00:49:18,074 --> 00:49:20,702
Punks like you being called President?

788
00:49:21,703 --> 00:49:25,456
What has this world come to?

789
00:49:25,457 --> 00:49:26,458
Oh, yes.

790
00:49:27,000 --> 00:49:28,751
Aren't you supposed to be in jail?

791
00:49:28,752 --> 00:49:32,588
Why? You got a problem with me being out?

792
00:49:32,589 --> 00:49:35,800
What? No.
That's not what I meant. Not at all.

793
00:49:37,802 --> 00:49:39,845
- Kang-sik.
- Yes, Boss.

794
00:49:39,846 --> 00:49:44,100
Now that I'm out after all this time,
I have a lot of questions.

795
00:49:44,517 --> 00:49:46,060
What kind of questions, Boss?

796
00:49:46,061 --> 00:49:49,104
How the world has changed
in the last ten years.

797
00:49:49,105 --> 00:49:53,276
Especially everything that happened
with Beom-ryong and Gong-bok.

798
00:49:53,943 --> 00:49:56,279
Tell me everything.

799
00:49:56,613 --> 00:49:58,490
You mean Beom-ryong, sir?

800
00:49:58,865 --> 00:50:01,409
That's right. Beom-ryong.

801
00:50:02,577 --> 00:50:03,870
Didn't you hear me?

802
00:50:04,871 --> 00:50:08,708
I need to know every detail

803
00:50:09,334 --> 00:50:11,711
on what kind of trouble
that runaway kid got into

804
00:50:12,504 --> 00:50:16,299
and who he was running around with.

805
00:50:17,842 --> 00:50:19,010
Sure.

806
00:50:33,233 --> 00:50:36,360
So, have you looked into the ferry case?

807
00:50:36,361 --> 00:50:38,862
Just as you suspected.

808
00:50:38,863 --> 00:50:41,990
An NIS agent and a spy
reportedly went missing on that ferry.

809
00:50:41,991 --> 00:50:43,784
They were reportedly
looking for a package.

810
00:50:43,785 --> 00:50:46,162
It contained information about a traitor
colluding with North Korea.

811
00:50:46,454 --> 00:50:48,497
The package vanished with them.

812
00:50:48,498 --> 00:50:50,625
A traitor colluding with North Korea?

813
00:50:52,085 --> 00:50:53,336
A package?

814
00:50:58,508 --> 00:51:00,593
So how was it all wrapped up?

815
00:51:01,511 --> 00:51:03,762
Deputy Director Han took personal command

816
00:51:03,763 --> 00:51:06,433
and he reportedly kept it
from leaking to the press or the police.

817
00:51:06,975 --> 00:51:10,853
What happened to those
involved in the case afterward

818
00:51:10,854 --> 00:51:12,522
was kept top secret, so nothing is known.

819
00:51:15,316 --> 00:51:17,777
My goodness. Jeez.

820
00:51:18,820 --> 00:51:20,947
The mole is Han Gyeong-wook. Right?

821
00:51:21,197 --> 00:51:24,617
And that package
must contain his weakness.

822
00:51:25,869 --> 00:51:28,287
- Deputy Director Han's weakness?
- Come on, can't you see?

823
00:51:28,288 --> 00:51:31,039
This is exactly
Deputy Director Han's MO, isn't it?

824
00:51:31,040 --> 00:51:33,293
When he fails to retrieve the package
containing his weakness

825
00:51:33,418 --> 00:51:36,712
he takes charge
and buries everyone involved.

826
00:51:36,713 --> 00:51:39,340
What do you think?
Doesn't this picture look familiar?

827
00:51:44,387 --> 00:51:45,388
No, but...

828
00:51:46,347 --> 00:51:50,518
But there's another very
interesting situation to consider here.

829
00:51:50,643 --> 00:51:52,311
Ten years ago

830
00:51:52,312 --> 00:51:55,772
the three people who disappeared
while looking for this package

831
00:51:55,773 --> 00:51:58,234
suddenly reappeared, hand in hand.

832
00:51:59,194 --> 00:52:01,488
What do you think that means?

833
00:52:03,573 --> 00:52:07,160
It means that the package with
Han Gyeong-wook's weakness has surfaced.

834
00:52:10,914 --> 00:52:12,247
Where are the hitmen now?

835
00:52:12,248 --> 00:52:13,750
They're keeping an eye on the three.

836
00:52:15,335 --> 00:52:18,795
There will be a time
when they take out the package.

837
00:52:18,796 --> 00:52:22,132
Tell them to tail them
without missing a single breath

838
00:52:22,133 --> 00:52:25,093
and do whatever it takes
to snatch that package at the right time.

839
00:52:25,094 --> 00:52:26,888
Yes, sir.

840
00:52:30,391 --> 00:52:32,851
The places Bong Je-sun went
are here and here.

841
00:52:32,852 --> 00:52:34,228
Here, here, here, and here.

842
00:52:34,229 --> 00:52:36,606
There aren't many, so it shouldn't
take long to check them all.

843
00:52:44,030 --> 00:52:45,907
- The receiver?
- Oh, one second.

844
00:52:48,576 --> 00:52:49,911
I can't read upside-down.

845
00:52:51,246 --> 00:52:53,081
What does he mean, "not many?"

846
00:52:59,254 --> 00:53:00,755
You've been all over the place.

847
00:53:12,267 --> 00:53:14,227
All right. Here it is.

848
00:53:15,103 --> 00:53:16,145
Well...

849
00:53:18,106 --> 00:53:19,482
Aren't you hungry?

850
00:53:20,066 --> 00:53:21,568
- I'm starving.
- I know, right?

851
00:53:22,235 --> 00:53:25,154
You missed lunch
because you were helping me.

852
00:53:32,829 --> 00:53:36,081
Seriously, who carries around ingredients
for chicken soup in their bag?

853
00:53:36,082 --> 00:53:37,833
I told you.

854
00:53:37,834 --> 00:53:39,793
I wanted to be helpful in any way I could.

855
00:53:39,794 --> 00:53:43,672
Cooking is the only thing I'm good at
so I packed some just in case.

856
00:53:43,673 --> 00:53:45,799
I'm glad they're coming in handy.

857
00:53:45,800 --> 00:53:47,844
Gosh, that looks delicious.

858
00:53:56,185 --> 00:53:58,562
So, how is it? Do you like it?

859
00:53:58,563 --> 00:54:00,063
But there's no black pepper.

860
00:54:00,064 --> 00:54:03,066
- Oh, I...
- No, but it's good enough.

861
00:54:03,067 --> 00:54:04,235
I think it's delicious.

862
00:54:05,778 --> 00:54:06,779
That's a relief.

863
00:54:07,822 --> 00:54:10,907
You stood up for me earlier.
I was really grateful.

864
00:54:10,908 --> 00:54:12,784
Hey, it was nothing.

865
00:54:12,785 --> 00:54:15,621
I mean, Jeong Ho-myeong
isn't usually that rash.

866
00:54:15,622 --> 00:54:18,749
He must be busy and feeling rushed lately
so he made a mistake.

867
00:54:18,750 --> 00:54:20,417
- Was it Bong Je-sun?
- Yes.

868
00:54:20,418 --> 00:54:22,628
- You should try and understand.
- Sure.

869
00:54:22,629 --> 00:54:25,714
Still, it was a very dangerous mistake,
don't you think?

870
00:54:25,715 --> 00:54:28,635
- Oh, it really was dangerous.
- Exactly.

871
00:54:39,646 --> 00:54:42,899
I almost spilled everything myself.

872
00:54:43,608 --> 00:54:44,734
- What?
- What?

873
00:54:50,156 --> 00:54:51,199
Wait.

874
00:55:06,172 --> 00:55:07,382
You saved me.

875
00:55:09,133 --> 00:55:10,385
Hold on.

876
00:55:12,136 --> 00:55:14,305
If it weren't for you guys,
things could have gotten messy.

877
00:55:36,327 --> 00:55:38,079
This ten-year-long ill-fated relationship

878
00:55:39,080 --> 00:55:40,580
and that darn package...

879
00:55:40,581 --> 00:55:43,084
Once you get a good night's sleep

880
00:55:46,003 --> 00:55:48,297
will all be gone.

881
00:56:09,318 --> 00:56:10,403
What should we do?

882
00:56:11,404 --> 00:56:12,739
Just tail him for now.

883
00:56:14,866 --> 00:56:18,453
You need black pepper for chicken soup.

884
00:56:23,750 --> 00:56:25,001
Hey!

885
00:56:25,626 --> 00:56:26,669
Hey!

886
00:56:27,211 --> 00:56:29,045
Hey, Gong-bok.

887
00:56:29,046 --> 00:56:32,341
Hey, Gong-bok, open your eyes! Wake up!

888
00:56:32,884 --> 00:56:34,927
- Darn it.
- Gosh, my head.

889
00:56:37,513 --> 00:56:39,806
- Hang on.
- Gosh, my head.

890
00:56:39,807 --> 00:56:41,642
What the? Where's Bulgae?

891
00:56:41,768 --> 00:56:44,060
Hey, the receiver!

892
00:56:44,061 --> 00:56:45,395
The receiver?

893
00:56:45,396 --> 00:56:46,647
Gosh, hold on.

894
00:56:47,774 --> 00:56:49,400
The receiver is gone.

895
00:56:51,110 --> 00:56:52,945
- What about the car key?
- The car key?

896
00:56:55,490 --> 00:56:56,741
The car key is gone too.

897
00:56:57,700 --> 00:56:59,243
Bulgae, that jerk!

898
00:56:59,452 --> 00:57:00,870
Darn it! Seriously.

899
00:57:48,835 --> 00:57:50,461
What's wrong?

900
00:57:51,629 --> 00:57:52,880
Hey, Bulgae!

901
00:57:55,049 --> 00:57:56,217
Looking for this?

902
00:57:58,803 --> 00:58:02,681
Gosh, Mr. Jeong, Mr. Gang, Mr. Ma.

903
00:58:02,682 --> 00:58:05,016
How... how did you get here?

904
00:58:05,017 --> 00:58:07,269
As for me...

905
00:58:07,270 --> 00:58:09,521
I thought I was starting
to remember something

906
00:58:09,522 --> 00:58:10,772
so I came here for a bit.

907
00:58:10,773 --> 00:58:13,901
Look at that disgusting face.

908
00:58:14,360 --> 00:58:17,405
Well played. You're a really good actor.

909
00:58:19,073 --> 00:58:20,282
Stop the act, you bastard.

910
00:58:20,283 --> 00:58:22,326
Hey, cut it out. We're on to you.

911
00:58:25,413 --> 00:58:27,498
I knew I should've used more of the drug.

912
00:58:30,209 --> 00:58:31,586
Darn it.

913
00:58:33,504 --> 00:58:35,130
How did you know to come here?

914
00:58:35,131 --> 00:58:36,966
I knew you'd pull something like this

915
00:58:37,925 --> 00:58:39,677
so I set up a little trick of my own.

916
00:58:54,650 --> 00:58:56,569
Hey, give that back now.
It belongs to my son.

917
00:58:59,697 --> 00:59:03,200
You darn scumbags. You dare mess with me?

918
00:59:04,577 --> 00:59:07,663
Look at that.
He's finally baring his fangs.

919
00:59:07,788 --> 00:59:09,956
Look at this two-faced jerk.

920
00:59:09,957 --> 00:59:12,668
Gosh, your true nature is coming out now.

921
00:59:13,169 --> 00:59:15,337
This is good. Very good.

922
00:59:15,338 --> 00:59:16,756
Hey, your acting was really...

923
00:59:17,882 --> 00:59:19,467
I almost fell for it.

924
00:59:20,051 --> 00:59:22,344
Did you really?

925
00:59:22,345 --> 00:59:24,055
Now, cut the crap.

926
00:59:24,513 --> 00:59:26,682
At first, I wasn't sure.

927
00:59:27,058 --> 00:59:30,602
But something about what happened
at the hospital kept bothering me.

928
00:59:30,603 --> 00:59:33,772
A guy who ditches a tracker and runs away

929
00:59:33,773 --> 00:59:35,815
suddenly comes back
and offers to help us with our job?

930
00:59:35,816 --> 00:59:37,317
Why would you do that?

931
00:59:37,318 --> 00:59:39,361
It was because
you didn't have the package.

932
00:59:39,362 --> 00:59:41,905
You only knew
the general area of the package

933
00:59:41,906 --> 00:59:43,574
not its exact location.

934
00:59:44,033 --> 00:59:46,827
So I decided to run a little test.

935
00:59:48,955 --> 00:59:51,206
A test? What kind of test?

936
00:59:51,207 --> 00:59:55,753
Hey, why do you think I'd invite
a dangerous guy like you to our hideout?

937
01:00:12,311 --> 01:00:14,563
I said go on ahead.
The three of us need to talk.

938
01:00:15,856 --> 01:00:17,858
I'll be in there, then.

939
01:00:20,486 --> 01:00:22,405
Man, those must be heavy.

940
01:00:41,465 --> 01:00:43,426
Where did they hide it?

941
01:00:45,761 --> 01:00:47,638
They've hidden it really well.

942
01:00:49,015 --> 01:00:50,266
Jeez.

943
01:00:53,060 --> 01:00:55,354
You must have needed this receiver.

944
01:00:56,355 --> 01:01:00,317
Coming here... Jeez, now I get it.

945
01:01:01,277 --> 01:01:02,361
So then...

946
01:01:02,737 --> 01:01:05,197
provoking me like a madman was also...

947
01:01:05,322 --> 01:01:08,074
I figured you'd move
as soon as you felt cornered.

948
01:01:08,075 --> 01:01:09,492
And...

949
01:01:09,493 --> 01:01:13,456
I also had a hunch
you'd ditch these idiots.

950
01:01:15,916 --> 01:01:17,459
Hey, what's that supposed to mean?

951
01:01:17,460 --> 01:01:19,794
If you knew that,
you should've told us beforehand.

952
01:01:19,795 --> 01:01:20,921
Hey.

953
01:01:21,672 --> 01:01:23,423
If you don't want to die,
hand over that receiver.

954
01:01:23,424 --> 01:01:25,050
This guy... He still doesn't get it.

955
01:01:25,051 --> 01:01:26,843
Hey, you think we have to give it to you
just because you ask?

956
01:01:26,844 --> 01:01:29,388
Why are we listening to him?
Let's just crush him already.

957
01:01:29,680 --> 01:01:33,059
Hey, Bulgae.
Why are you after the package?

958
01:01:34,518 --> 01:01:36,311
That USB drive
with Han Gyeong-wook's weakness

959
01:01:36,312 --> 01:01:37,730
is useless to you.

960
01:01:38,647 --> 01:01:40,440
What you're after

961
01:01:40,441 --> 01:01:43,444
is the North Korean slush fund
that Black Pearl brought.

962
01:01:43,986 --> 01:01:45,362
Slush fund?

963
01:01:47,907 --> 01:01:49,783
Slush fund? What are you talking about?

964
01:01:49,784 --> 01:01:51,493
- I'll give it all to you.
- Mr. Jeong. But...

965
01:01:51,494 --> 01:01:53,119
Hey, how much is it?

966
01:01:53,120 --> 01:01:55,081
You can't just make a decision
on something important by yourself!

967
01:01:55,206 --> 01:01:57,333
It's not like we need it anyway.

968
01:01:58,375 --> 01:02:01,504
In return, you'll cooperate with us.

969
01:02:02,546 --> 01:02:06,133
If you help us drive Han Gyeong-wook
out of Yeongseon Island

970
01:02:06,342 --> 01:02:10,221
I'll give you the entire slush fund
after it's all over.

971
01:02:14,892 --> 01:02:17,394
- And you expect me to believe that?
- Make your choice!

972
01:02:19,105 --> 01:02:21,147
If you run away now

973
01:02:21,148 --> 01:02:23,191
your nephew Heo Nam-il on Yeongseon Island

974
01:02:23,192 --> 01:02:25,026
the K-pop dance club members
who helped you

975
01:02:25,027 --> 01:02:28,614
and even Prosecutor Gang
could all get hurt by Han Gyeong-wook.

976
01:02:29,281 --> 01:02:30,866
And you don't want that to happen, do you?

977
01:02:33,160 --> 01:02:36,955
How would you know
if Han Gyeong-wook will hurt Nam-il?

978
01:02:36,956 --> 01:02:40,291
Gosh, this idiot is so paranoid.

979
01:02:40,292 --> 01:02:42,418
See for yourself

980
01:02:42,419 --> 01:02:44,839
just how serious this situation is.

981
01:02:46,799 --> 01:02:48,717
Come out, you rats!

982
01:02:49,969 --> 01:02:51,220
What the hell are you saying?

983
01:02:57,601 --> 01:03:00,145
Mr. Jeong, who are they?

984
01:03:00,146 --> 01:03:01,354
I don't know.

985
01:03:01,355 --> 01:03:03,648
They've been following us
from the camper van.

986
01:03:03,649 --> 01:03:05,650
Hey, we've been tailed this whole time?

987
01:03:05,651 --> 01:03:06,944
You think they were just tailing us?

988
01:03:08,654 --> 01:03:11,448
You're the ones
who messed with the camper, aren't you?

989
01:03:16,704 --> 01:03:19,081
You left traces all over the place.

990
01:03:29,049 --> 01:03:32,469
Hey, did Han Gyeong-wook send those guys?

991
01:03:33,387 --> 01:03:35,430
Sneaking around
and testing the waters like a rat

992
01:03:35,431 --> 01:03:36,891
isn't Han Gyeong-wook's style.

993
01:03:40,519 --> 01:03:41,603
Hey!

994
01:03:41,604 --> 01:03:43,189
You should at least introduce yourselves.

995
01:03:44,064 --> 01:03:45,481
Who sent you?

996
01:03:45,482 --> 01:03:46,858
None of your business.

997
01:03:46,859 --> 01:03:51,322
Hand over the receiver or whatever it is
that can find the package.

998
01:03:51,906 --> 01:03:53,364
Then I'll spare your lives.

999
01:03:53,365 --> 01:03:56,368
What kind of crap are these rats spouting?

1000
01:03:56,493 --> 01:03:59,329
Let's just take them all out,
Bulgae and these scumbags.

1001
01:03:59,330 --> 01:04:00,331
Hey, Bulgae.

1002
01:04:00,831 --> 01:04:02,082
Now make your choice.

1003
01:04:02,750 --> 01:04:05,377
You can either fight against us

1004
01:04:06,253 --> 01:04:09,173
or join us and fight against them.

1005
01:04:21,310 --> 01:04:24,021
SPECIAL THANKS
TO KIM SANG-KYUNG AND KWON YUL

1006
01:04:38,619 --> 01:04:39,702
Found it.

1007
01:04:39,703 --> 01:04:41,454
We've detected a signal
trying to decrypt the package.

1008
01:04:41,455 --> 01:04:43,206
- So it wasn't a bluff?
- Hey!

1009
01:04:43,207 --> 01:04:44,540
- Are you sure you can crack this?
- Huh?

1010
01:04:44,541 --> 01:04:47,001
- This thing isn't easy to open.
- It's almost done.

1011
01:04:47,002 --> 01:04:48,461
- It's 2%.
- Hey, don't touch it.

1012
01:04:48,462 --> 01:04:50,046
If you're trying
to pull a fast one on me...

1013
01:04:50,047 --> 01:04:51,172
We shouldn't be
fighting amongst ourselves!

1014
01:04:51,173 --> 01:04:52,382
The boss got out of prison.

1015
01:04:52,383 --> 01:04:54,092
Bring me that package.

1016
01:04:54,093 --> 01:04:55,593
What if they decide
to side with the thugs?

1017
01:04:55,594 --> 01:04:57,845
You want me to stab my boss
in the back after all this time?

1018
01:04:57,846 --> 01:05:00,181
- Go back to the convenience store.
- I'll step aside.

1019
01:05:00,182 --> 01:05:01,266
Boss!

1020
01:05:01,267 --> 01:05:03,101
- A family?
- Do whatever it takes...

1021
01:05:03,102 --> 01:05:04,185
Get rid of them all.

1022
01:05:04,186 --> 01:05:05,645
What if your family gets hurt first?

1023
01:05:05,646 --> 01:05:07,105
- Ji-woo?
- Dad.

1024
01:05:07,106 --> 01:05:09,065
You don't mind
never seeing your nephew again?

1025
01:05:09,066 --> 01:05:11,526
You think I'd let some useless emotion
hold me back now?

1026
01:05:11,527 --> 01:05:13,027
All I have to do is hand over the package?

1027
01:05:13,028 --> 01:05:15,446
Isn't it a shame?
After all your hard work.

1028
01:05:15,447 --> 01:05:16,572
I'm prepared.

1029
01:05:16,573 --> 01:05:18,324
Let those punks come at us.

1030
01:05:18,325 --> 01:05:19,701
There's nothing we can't do.

1031
01:05:19,702 --> 01:05:21,120
We have to finish this.
